This paper focuses on human-robot interaction and planning in remote settings, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). It also discusses the human factors involved in the interaction, such as mental workload and situation awareness, which are important topics in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The incorporation of planning capability into the robot involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the investigation of trade-offs between different types of remote human-robot teaming involves optimization and decision-making (cs.MA).
